narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Profound but intensive knowledge of ancient civilizations and their ritual experiences, methods for analyzing sensory experiences
I started to think about sensoriality in ancient societies, and acquired some insights into interdisciplinarity by listening to the comments of researchers and graduate students from other fields.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: One week was just simply not enough for one civilization. If this very course were to be offered in the future, I think it would be better to focus on fewer cultures but in more depth.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, it is a great course to learn about cultures that usually fall out of the standard class themes, from the Mayas to China.
